{
  "texts": [
    "The model can be retrieved via the Hugging Face platform.",
    "Semantic similarity analyses were conducted in Python (version 3.11.5) with the SentenceTransformer package (version 2.2.2) (Reimers & Gurevych, 2019), and semantic distance was measure using cosine similarity.",
    "We then compared the distribution of distances between humans and GPT-4.",
    "In general, we did not find that human reappraisals adhere more closely to the vignette than reappraisals generated by GPT-4 (Mann-Whitney-U: study 1: U = 18714.0, p = 0.79; study 2: U = 288905.0, p = 0.87; study 4: U = 20483.0, p = 0.09).",
    "Figure 6 shows the distribution of cosine similarities between reappraisals and vignettes for Studies 1, 2 and 4 (Study 3 used the reappraisals that were produced in Study 2)."
  ]
}